This article is a transcript of President Obama's remarks during a visit with the 2015 WNBA Championship Minnesota Lynx basketball team at the White House. The President congratulated the team on their third visit to the White House in five years and praised their success. He also recognized Flip Saunders, a supporter of the team who passed away, and spoke about the team's resilience and community involvement. The President highlighted the importance of the WNBA and its players as role models for young girls, and expressed his support for equal pay for equal work.